<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="S" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Scholar" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Scholar,</orth> 1) a schoolboy: <cit><quote>I am no breeching s. in the schools,</quote> <bibl n="shak. shr 3.1.18" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. III, 1, 18</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) one who learns of a teacher, a pupil, disciple: <cit><quote>he is a better s. than I thought,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 4.1.82" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. IV, 1, 82</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>my cousin William is become a good s.</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 3.2.11" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B III, 2, 11</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>thy master dies thy s.</quote> <bibl n="shak. ant 4.14.102" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. IV, 14, 102</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. per 2.3.17" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. II, 3, 17</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 2.5.31" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 5, 31</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 2.5.31" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 5, 31</bibl> <bibl n="shak. per 4.6.198" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 6, 198</bibl>.
<lb />3) a man of letters: <bibl n="shak. wiv 2.2.186" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. II, 2, 186</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 3.2.154" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. III, 2, 154</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 4.2.9" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL IV, 2, 9</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 1.2.124" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. I, 2, 124</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 4.1.10" default="NO" valid="yes">As IV, 1, 10</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 1.2.159" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. I, 2, 159</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 2.79.159" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 79</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 2.3.13" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. II, 3, 13</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 4.2.12" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 12</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 1.1.32" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 I, 1, 32</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.4.36" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B IV, 4, 36</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 2.2.113" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 II, 2, 113</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 4.2.51" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 51</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 1.5.141" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 5, 141</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 3.1.159" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 159</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 2.1.167" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. II, 1, 167</bibl>. <cit><quote>I would to God some s. would conjure her,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 2.1.264" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado II, 1, 264</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>thou art a s., speak to it,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 1.1.42" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 1, 42</bibl></cit> (Latin being the language of conjurers and exorcists).
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>